The paper deals with the problem of sampling from Gibbs distributions induced by weighted local CSPs in the LOCAL model, which is a distributed computing model. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses Markov chain based distributed algorithms, which involve probability and randomness, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions the use of algorithms for sampling, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of constructing locally checkable labelings, which is related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
